cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the problem of global localization for mobile vehicles using LiDAR point clouds. The problem is related to robotics and autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also presents a semi-handcrafted representation learning method for LiDAR point clouds, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach involves similarity modeling, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.RO, cs.CV, and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI and cs.CL.
